import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of deaths over the years?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    grouped_data = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    grouped_data.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Entity')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths across different entities?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('Year').sum().reset_index()
    average_deaths = data['Deaths'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'], label='Deaths')
    plt.axhline(y=average_deaths, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {average_deaths:.2f}')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths per year?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].sum().pct_change() * 100
    data.plot(kind='line')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the percentage change in deaths over the years?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
